# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Wrath of God — scripted board wipe (DestroyAll + NoRegen).
#
# Closed issue mtg-558 closed Wrath of God as WORKING. Aspects:
#   - SP$ DestroyAll | ValidCards$ Creature | NoRegen$ True
#   - Destroys ALL creatures regardless of controller; each goes to its owner's
#     graveyard (CR 701.7 Destroy).
#   - NoRegen$ True: the destroyed creatures cannot be regenerated.
#
# Wave 1 had to drive Wrath with a hand-written `--p1-fixed-inputs` CLI string
# (see the mtg-558 reproducer). This puzzle backs it inside the bulk runner via
# a [p0_script], asserting that creatures BOTH players control die.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Wrath of God in hand, 2 Plains + 2 generic-capable lands (Mountains).
#         Also controls a Grizzly Bears (so we prove it kills OWN creatures too).
#   - P1: controls a Savannah Lions (1/1) and a Black Knight.
#   - Script: P0 casts Wrath of God. All three creatures are destroyed.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Wrath of God Board Wipe
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Wrath of God, destroying ALL creatures regardless of controller — including P0's own Grizzly Bears and P1's Savannah Lions + Black Knight. Backs issue mtg-558 (SP$ DestroyAll ValidCards$ Creature NoRegen$ True, CR 701.7).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Wrath of God
p0battlefield=Plains;Plains;Mountain;Mountain;Grizzly Bears
p0library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Savannah Lions;Black Knight
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Cast the board wipe. DestroyAll has no target, so a bare `cast` suffices.
cast Wrath of God

[assertions]
# The sorcery was actually cast.
spell cast Wrath of God
# The destroyed creatures went to their owners' graveyards (durable final-state).
# Wrath is symmetric: P0's OWN Grizzly Bears is in P0's graveyard...
me graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
# ...and both of P1's creatures are in P1's graveyard.
opponent graveyard contains Savannah Lions
opponent graveyard contains Black Knight
# NOTE: we do NOT assert the `creature died` EVENT here. That event is only
# emitted on LETHAL-DAMAGE deaths (combat or burn); a creature removed by a
# DestroyAll effect goes to the graveyard without firing CreatureDied. The
# destruction itself is fully verified by the graveyard-contains assertions
# above (and the "is destroyed" / NoRegen marker in the golden log). The
# missing event for destroy-based deaths is tracked as mtg-ngf7s, not a
# Wrath of God card defect.
